sp.p:
              
              There is a groat, go drink a pint of Sack,

              Comfort thyself thou art not well in thy wits; 

              God forbid, pay me ten pound not due to me.

div2.stage:
Enter at one dore the Queene, Lecester, Suffex, Lords, Gresham; 
at the other Cassemer, the French and Florentine
Ambassadours, Sir Tho: Ramsey, &c.

sp.p:
              
              As of all men, we are mortal, made of clay,

              Now healthful, now crazy; now sick, now well; 

              Now live, now dead, and then to heaven, or hell.

              
              O sir, the love I bear you makes me chary

              Of your good name, your credit is dear to me; 

              You never were condemned for anything,

              Since I had first acquaintance with your name; 

              As now you are, you have done a deed this day,

              That hath from you taken all good thoughts away.

              
              He is by this, half way to Tyburne gone; 

              The suit was followed in Iohn Greshams name,

              How can you then avow you know it not?

              
              That you call duty we accept as love,

              And we do thank you, nay we thank you all; 

              It is not to one, but it is in general.
